<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=101727269419106></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101727269419106><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=101727269419106>RE: looking into the class</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=101727269419106#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122349><span id=Scholar>Friar Melifaunt</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>36 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Mar 27th 6:48 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.07]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well now that Verant has changed the class somewhat it is even more exciting: the scales have been lifted from our eyes (no more spellbook), and our baby rezzes make us even more valuable to groups.<br><br>Boring? Never! You are constantly facing questions of life &amp; death in groups? Low mana, suddenly overwhelmed by monsters, the enchanter is getting hit and the main tank is yelling &quot;Heal me! Heal me!&quot; while the wizard goes link dead. Who do you save?<br>a. cast divine aura and run for it?<br>b. save the enchanter by rooting the mob?<br>c. heal the enchanter and possibly draw aggro on your own divine butt?<br>d. heal the tank and hope his taunt saves your ass too?<br><br>And decide your answer in 3 seconds or less, or all of you will die.<br><br>I love this kind of pressure!<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

